a broken sample is NOT good. We should fail release testing without fixing this
in any case...

a little more info... this sample fails because we try to make an inter-type
declaration of Point.compareTo(Object) from the Comparable interface, but in
Java 5, Comparable (and the compareTo method) have a generic signature that we
don't understand yet. So really this is an aj5m3 bug, but I'm going to keep
looking for a little bit longer since I don't like a broken sample.

Fix available, see download page:
